review_blob: Copper pour with a decent off white head. Smoky fireplace aroma, bit of malt. Taste is slight sweetness, smoky barbecued meat
Dark red/brown pour with a huge orange head, which collapses into puffy marshmallow. Spicy, pine, orange aromas, taste is spicy, bitter, piney/resiny, dry and peppery
Deep brown, almost black pour with a decent tan head. Piney, tropical fruit, chocolate aromas. Taste is sweet, chocolate, tiny bit of coffee, pine and nice long but light bitterness. Pretty damn good

Slightly cloudy amber pour with a thin white head. Aroma is grapefruit and passionfruit, bit of caramel. Taste is slightly sweet at the start with resiny bitterness, a bit of caramel, passionfruit. Like this one more than the citra - bit more gutsy
beer_name: The Little Brewing Co Galaxy IPA

review_blob: Cloudy amber pour with a thin white head. Passionfruit, orange and caramel aromas. Taste is slightly sweet, biscuit, orange and a little passionfruit, nice long, light bitter finish
beer_name: The Little Brewing Co Citra IPA

review_blob: Cola coloured pour with a thin off-white head. Nice, roasty, grapefruit and pine aromas. Taste is burnt sugar, slight bit of roast, pine, decent bitterness and a little toffee at the end. A little thin (fairly light ABV for a black IPA, and flavour-wise it sits somewhere between that and a pale ale) but very smashable.
beer_name: Black Hops Call of Duty Black Hops III Midnight Pale Ale

review_blob: Light gold with a thin white head, lots of tiny little floaters. Bread, hay and a little herbal aroma. Taste is sweet malts, low bitterness, a bit of tropical fruit. Im a bit underwhelmed by it, but it is also quite drinkable. Confusing.
beer_name: Mad River Steelhead Extra Pale Ale

review_blob: Pale gold pour with a fluffy white head. Sweet, malty, slightly cardboardy aroma. Doesnt smell quite as terrible as most generic macros. Taste is malt, thin, watery, sweet, not really much flavour. Not as terrible as some but not great.
Pale, super fizzy pour with thin white head. Wet cardboard, nasty metallic aromas. Taste is thin malty sweet macro lager rubbish.
Pale straw colour. Pretty straight up apple juice aroma. Taste was slightly sweet, slightly tart, crisp, dries out a touch at the end

Deep gold with a 1cm, long lasting white head. Bready, earthy, slightly floral aromas.Taste is crisp, grainy, bread,a little floral note but with a slight chemical twang. Its not bad, theres just a slight aftertaste that I cant put my finger on that isnt great. Smells better than it tastes.
Black pour with a thick beige head. Roasty, chocolatey, citrus aromas. Taste is sweetish, dark chocolate, roasty, and decent whack of bitterness at the end
Golden pour with a thin white head. Slight orange, pine aromas but not overwhelming, caramel. Taste is caramel, tropical fruit and pretty decent bitterness.
Deep brown pour with a thin tan head. Toffee, coffee and chocolate armas. Taste is sweetish, malty, coffee, chocolate, a little dried fruit
Orange-gold pour with a big off-white head. Big citrus aroma, grapefruit and orange, caramel. Taste is sweet, caramel, grapefruit, tropical fruits, finishes quite bitter
From Aug 2015. Deep gold, slightly cloudy, decent off-white head. Citrus, caramel, biscuity on the nose. Similar tastes, decent whack of bitterness and a little booze
Murky gold pour with a huge, overflowing pale orange head. Pepper, orange, apricot, a little funkiness on the nose. Sweet start, orange, slightly bitter, spicy, interesting mix
Pale gold, a little cloudy, no head. Flowery, citrussy, light and slightly tart aroma. Lemony, grassy, light bitterness, a little spicy.
Clear, light gold with a big fluffy white head. Tropical fruits - passionfruit, pineapple, and a bit of caramel. Malty, pine and passionfruit, fairly big hit of resiny bitterness.
Dark amber with a thin off white head which fades quickly. Toffee/burnt sugar aroma, sweet dried fruit as well. Taste is malty, slightly burnt sugar, not much else.

Light gold with a big fizzy white head, lots of carbonation. Grainy, slightly nasty chemical smell, little bit of floral and citrus. Taste is grain, citrus, fairly heavy bitterness, a bit of a nasty chemical taste too
Deep red-brown with decent pale brown head. Toffee, slightly fruity, nutty aroma. Taste is burnt caramel, nuts, slightly bitter.
Pale, pale straw colour. Sweet apple and winey smell. Very clean, crisp apple juice, slightly tart, mostly sweet. Not too shabby
Pale yellow pour with a quickly dissipating head. Sweet, grainy, grassy aroma. Taste is a little lemony, grassy, bready.

Slightly cloudy orange pour with a thick, tight, off white head. Caramel, citrus, passionfruit and apricot aromas. Taste is sweet caramel, passionfruit, apricot, decent amount of bitterness, a little boozy
beer_name: Noisy Minor Bad Wolf Imperial IPA

review_blob: Orange gold pour with a thick, long-lasting white head. Orange, grassy, slightly manky aroma. Sweet malts, bitter orange/marmalade and a bit of a chemical tinge to it, ok but nothing flash

Deep brick red pour with a decent tan head.Huge citrus, stonefruit, passionfruit, caramel aromas. Taste is initially, sweetish, fruity, malty, then big peach, passionfruit, resiny, nice bitterness comes through but not overwhelming, just beautifully balanced beer.

bit of a big soapy pour - over a nice amber colour. Big tropical aroma, caramel, but massive fruit in there. Sweet caramel with lots of citrus, peach and pine, nice bitterness cuts through it all. Marmaladey, bitter finish
Pale gold with a nice thick white head. Grassy, tropical fruits, funky aromas. Taste is slightly sour, good bitterness, winey, spice, yeasty funk. Its a good one

hazy pale gold pour with a fluffy white head. Peaches! Massive peachy aroma up front with a fruit cocktail smell like a can of SPC mixed fruit has just been opened up. Taste is more pineapple, grainy, smooth, bready, peach and apricot, nice bitterness to finish.

Deep amber/red pour with a thin tan head. Malty, caramel, dried fruit, and a bit of a weird chemical aroma. Taste is toffee, dried fruit, plum. Seems a bit thin. Its not terrible, but I still havent really had a beer from this mob that has lived up to their hype.

Slightly cloudy, brick red pour with a decent light tan head. Malty, toasty, pine aromas. Taste is overwhelmingly malty, caramel, sweetish at first and then nice pine bitterness cuts through that really quickly. Not too shabby

Slightly hazy, orange gold pour with a 5mm head, quickly dissipates. Big tropical fruit punch nose, sweet, mango, pineapple, orange, caramel. Sweet caramel and mango, citrus, bitterness kicks in shortly after, finishes bitter, slightly dry
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Beer Camp Tropical IPA

review_blob: Black, decent tan head that dissipates fairly quickly. Chocolate, vanilla and cinnamon aromas, sweetish, spicy - smells amazing. Taste - it takes me back to mexican chocolate shops, the cinnamon, chilli, sweet (but not too sweet) chocolate, vanilla, hot chocolate/milky goodness. Love it.
beer_name: Chris Banker / Insurgente / Stone Xocoveza Mocha Stout

review_blob: Black pour with a thin tan head. Massive, dark chocolate/cocoa aroma, coffee, vanilla, sweetish but not cloying aromas. Taste is smooth, mocha, almost milky, hides the alcohol well, caramel, almost milky flavours, with a little heat from the chilli at the end. Sweet, slightly roasty, coffee bitterness, thick, creamy mouthfeel. As it warms up the booze is marginally more noticeable but all of the other flavours come up a notch too. Holy shit.
Pale yellow pour with a huge fluffy white head. Malt and a fair whack of lemon on the nose. Taste is crisp, malty, a good bit of hoppy bitterness in there too
Black pour with a nice tight tan head. Roasty, plummy, dried fruit aromas. Taste is port winey, dark fruit, toffee, roast, dark chocolate, nice burnt/roasty bitterness
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Dark Truth Stout

review_blob: Brown, hazy, flat looking. It doesnt look great. Then the aroma - caramel, candi sugar, honey - loads of sweet stuff. Taste is sweetish, with vanilla, booziness, honey and toffee, dried fruit. Pretty damn good
Dark brown pour with a thin off white head. Coffee, vanilla, chocolate and a little dark/burnt caramel aroma. Taste is similar, but sweetish finish

Murky, pinky pour with a thin white head. Aroma is cherries, yeast, red berries and a little funky. Taste is sour, funky, cherries. As it warms up, the funky elements are more dominant but that solid sour cherry taste still holds its own.
Cola pour with a thin tan head. Aroma of roast, coffee, liquorice, cocoa. Flavour is a little heavier on the chocolate, nice roasty flavour too and a little bitter at the finish

Cola coloured pour with a thick, puffy beige head. As it settles down, there is a big, yeast aroma, dried fruit, sweet malt. The taste is plummy, jammy, raisins, caramel, a little spice. As it warms up the dried fruit is more apparent, as is the booze.

Murky brown pour, flat looking and fairly unattractive. Sweet, toffee aroma, I get cola but that may be the childhood association with the RC Cola label. Bourbon, sweet boozy notes too. Taste is smooth, very low carbonation, vanilla, very rich toffee, chocolate, vanilla, bourbon. It looks like shit but tastes absolutely beautiful. Long, sweet toffee finish with a little booze. Good one to savour
Orange pour with minimal off-white head. Piney, woody, citrus aromas. Very light carbonation, slightly boozy flavour, pine, woody, spicy, very dry finish with nice bitterness.

Pale amber with a thick white head, big amount of fizz on opening. Passionfruit, pine, biscuity malt aromas. Taste is passionfruit, pine and a little spice, nice bitterness and pretty decent for a 3.5, packs a bit more punch than expected
Golden pour with a decent white head. Big passionfruit and citrus aroma with a bit of malt. Malty, biscuity, orange, tropical fruit and nice bit of bitterness
Hazy, pale gold pour with very thin head. Smoky, leathery, tart citrus aromas. Taste is tart, smoky, citrus, slightly sour, salt and pepper. Sour finish

Cloudy orange pour with a thin, tight white head. Aroma is orange, sour cherry, grass. Taste is sour, slightly bitter orange, salty, with orange juice burp aftertaste - nice and light, refreshing, great summer beer
beer_name: Anderson Valley Highway 128 Blood Orange Gose

review_blob: Black pour with a thick tan head. Big, dried fruit, burnt sugar, roasty malt aromas. Taste is roast, cocoa, booze, a little vanilla. Great beer
beer_name: Boatrocker Ramjet Whisky Barrel Aged Imperial Stout

review_blob: Black pour with a thick tan head. Huge sweet, chocolate, nutty, vanilla aroma. Taste is similar - creamy, bittersweet choc milk, nuts - but it fades fairly quickly
